solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    string reformatNumber(string number) {
        string digits;
        for (char c : number) {
            if (isdigit(c)) digits += c;
        }
        int n = digits.size();
        string res;
        int i = 0;
        while (i < n) {
            if (i) res += '-';
            int rem = n - i;
            if (rem > 4) {
                res += digits.substr(i, 3);
                i += 3;
            } else if (rem == 4) {
                res += digits.substr(i, 2) + '-' + digits.substr(i + 2, 2);
                break;
            } else {
                res += digits.substr(i, rem);
                break;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(N)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Collect digits in one pass, then build the result by greedily taking 3-digit blocks until ≤4 digits remain, handling the final 4 digits as two 2-digit blocks. Single linear scan and minimal extra memory.

